<li id="cite_note-LadaReid2-9">^ <a href="#cite_ref-LadaReid2_9-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-LadaReid2_9-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-LadaReid2_9-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-LadaReid2_9-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLadaReid1978">Lada, Charles J.; Reid, Mark J. (January 1, 1978). "CO observations of a molecular cloud complex associated with the bright rim near VY Canis Majoris". <i>The Astrophysical Journal</i> (American Astronomical Society) <b>219</b>: 95-104.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=CO+observations+of+a+molecular+cloud+complex+associated+with+the+bright+rim+near+VY+Canis+Majoris&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Astrophysical+Journal&amp;rft.aulast=Lada&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+J.&amp;rft.au=Lada%2C+Charles+J.&amp;rft.au=Reid%2C+Mark+J.&amp;rft.date=January+1%2C+1978&amp;rft.volume=219&amp;rft.pages=95-104&amp;rft.pub=American+Astronomical+Society&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:VY_Canis_Majoris"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Robinson-10">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Robinson_10-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Robinson_10-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Robinson_10-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRobinson1971">Robinson, L. J. (December 7, 1971). "Three somewhat overlooked facets of VY Canis Majoris". <i>Commission 27 of the I. A. U., Information Bulletin on Variable Stars</i> (Konkoly Observatory, Budapest) (599).</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Three+somewhat+overlooked+facets+of+VY+Canis+Majoris&amp;rft.jtitle=Commission+27+of+the+I.+A.+U.%2C+Information+Bulletin+on+Variable+Stars&amp;rft.aulast=Robinson&amp;rft.aufirst=L.+J.&amp;rft.au=Robinson%2C+L.+J.&amp;rft.date=December+7%2C+1971&amp;rft.issue=599&amp;rft.pub=Konkoly+Observatory%2C+Budapest&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:VY_Canis_Majoris"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Pogge2006-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Pogge2006_11-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFPogge2006">Pogge, Richard W. (October 31, 2006). <a href="http://www.astronomy.ohio-state.edu/~pogge/Ast162/Unit1/distances.html" class="external text" title="http://www.astronomy.ohio-state.edu/~pogge/Ast162/Unit1/distances.html" rel="nofollow">"Stellar distances"</a>. <i>Astronomy 162: Introduction to Stars, Galaxies and the Universe</i>. Ohio State University<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.astronomy.ohio-state.edu/~pogge/Ast162/Unit1/distances.html" class="external free" title="http://www.astronomy.ohio-state.edu/~pogge/Ast162/Unit1/distances.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.astronomy.ohio-state.edu/~pogge/Ast162/Unit1/distances.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on March 20, 2009</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Stellar+distances&amp;rft.atitle=Astronomy+162%3A+Introduction+to+Stars%2C+Galaxies+and+the+Universe&amp;rft.aulast=Pogge&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+W.&amp;rft.au=Pogge%2C+Richard+W.&amp;rft.date=October+31%2C+2006&amp;rft.pub=Ohio+State+University&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.astronomy.ohio-state.edu%2F%7Epogge%2FAst162%2FUnit1%2Fdistances.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:VY_Canis_Majoris"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
